# Content collections (`src/content/`)

Schemas live in `src/content.config.ts` (Zod from `astro/zod`, `image()` for assets).

## Collections and required frontmatter

| Collection | Folder | Required fields |
|------------|--------|-----------------|
| `team` | `src/content/team/` | `name`, `role`, `intro`, `education` (string array), `experience` (string array), `avatar.url`, `avatar.alt` |
| `services` | `src/content/services/` | `service`, `description` |
| `work` | `src/content/work/` | `launchDate`, `client`, `work`, `description`, `logo.url`, `logo.alt` |
| `legal` | `src/content/legal/` | `page`, `pubDate` |
| `posts` | `src/content/posts/` | `title`, `pubDate`, `description`, `image.url`, `image.alt`, `tags` (string array) |

## Templates (copy an existing file)

- `src/content/posts/1.md`, `src/content/work/1.md`, `src/content/team/1.md`, `src/content/services/web-dev.md`, `src/content/legal/terms.md`

## Images

- Use paths Astro’s content layer accepts with `image()` (e.g. under `src/images/` as in existing entries). Do not switch to broken relative paths without checking `astro:assets` / layout usage (`Image` components expect valid sources).

## Discipline

- New required keys → update `src/content.config.ts` **and** all layouts/cards that read that collection’s `data`.
- Entry **id** (URL segment) comes from the filename / glob loader — keep names URL-safe if you care about slugs (`/blog/posts/my-post`, `/legal/terms`, etc.).
